description:
"Okay, So It's Not Such a Wonderful Life" - starring Daredevil

Daredevil is confronted with overwhelming plot devices. To solve his woes, he tries to kill himself. Instead of dying, however, he is treated to what life would be like if other Marvel writers took control of his life.
 

"What Is Your New Years Resolution?"

Various Marvel characters give their resolutions for a new year.
 

"This Man, This Meal" - starring She-Bulk

The She-Bulk takes on a grocery store of killer food.
 

"Hazards of Being a Super-Hero"

A quick survey of problems various heroes have to live with as a result of their awesome powers.
 

"Auld Lang Syne"

Everyone, and that means everyone, is at Bud's Suds to celebrate the New Year. But will everyone survive Mr. Hide's bomb attack?
name: Okay, So It's Not Such A Wonderful Life

description:
"Tangled" starring Spittle-Man

Comic gimmicks are brought to the fore as a crazed baby duck seeks Spittle-Man for a battle. 
 

"Super Villain Dating Game"

Three eligible villains try to get lucky with Trixie Larue.
 

"Hazards of Being a Super Hero"

Various situations in which being awesome can be a real drag.
 

"Jurassic Classic" starring Milk and Cookies

Milk tries to save America's classic teen from tooth decay.
 

"Brain Games" starring the Visionary and the Scarlet Itch

The Visionary needs a new brain. Fortunately, the mall is a great place to get a new one.
 

"Forbush, P.I."

Forbush must find out who's trying to kill him before he gets killed.

description: 'Welcome Back to Riverdale.' Last issue, the memory of 'bad boy' Nick St. Clair was evoked by a lothario lifeguard - and lingered like the crumb of a fish sandwich Jughead left behind! This issue, Nick himself is back for sure, but for how long? The seemingly 'new and improved' Nick makes sure to apologize to everyone he wronged in the popular 'Bad Boy Trouble' story, but not everyone is convinced that he's changed - until he saves Betty from a rough gang of bikers! Will this lead to a brand-new romance for Betty?

description:
The Abomination tells a depressed woman the fairytale version of his life, as well as his unusual origin.

In the Doc Samson backup story, he has multiple confrontations with Psychobabble, a patient with multiple personality disorder. Each personality has it's own form and super-powers. Many forms have their own plans and counter-plans.
name: Abominable Tales

description:
Witness the birth of the monster as the origin of the Hulk is re-told!

At a bomb testing site in the New Mexico desert, scientist Bruce Banner, along with military personel, prepare to test launch Banner's new Gamma bomb. The project keeps mysteriously being delayed by Igor Raminski, an assistant on the project from Russia.

Part of that delay turns out to be a teenager named Rick Jones, who trespasses on the test site after being manipulated by Igor, in the form of another teenager. Igor is really a Skull in disguise.

After Rick succeeds in getting onto the test site, Dr. Banner sees him in the danger zone and rushes out to get him out of there before the bomb goes off, but General Ross goes ahead with the launch at the specific time, despite Banner being out there. The radiation nearly kills him, and eventually turns him into the Hulk.

The Hulk and Rick escape their hunters, only to be captured by Igor the Skull, who takes the duo to Russia to his partner's base, where they find the Gargoyle, a Russian scientist who wants to use the radiation to reverse his own Gargoyle transformation. The procedure works, but the Gargoyle (now in his human form) is killed by Russian soldiers who invade the complex, and Bruce and Rick escape with their lives, but not with a cure.
name: Birth of a Monster

description:
Overview

It's The Hulk vs. The Avengers! 'Nuff said! A rampaging Hulk hits Manhattan, making a bee-line for the Earth's Mightiest Heroes! You'll never believe what he wants, or what his cousin She-Hulk will have to do to stop him! Like THOR 2000, THUNDERBOLTS 2000, AVENGERS 2000 and IRON MAN 2000 this Annual is written by the series' ongoing writer, notice a pattern?
name: Basic Instinct
